cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper is about designing a control plane for data center networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a hybrid control plane design. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper addresses scalability issues in data center networks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper may touch on security and hardware aspects of the proposed design.
